            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "Upgrading from composition shingles to [link:/services/tile-roofs|concrete or clay tile] represents a significant investment but delivers compelling long-term value for homeowners planning extended ownership. A 2,000 sq ft shingle replacement costs $13,000-$17,000 with 20-25 year lifespan. The same roof in lightweight concrete tiles costs $17,600-$24,000 but lasts 40-50 years. Over 50 years of homeownership, shingles require replacement twice (original plus one future replacement at $20,000-$25,000 future cost), totaling $33,000-$42,000. Tile requires one installation delivering 50+ year protection, totaling $17,600-$24,000—a savings of $15,400-$18,000 over the same period. Additional benefits include 25-35% lower cooling costs (saving $400-$650 annually in Tucson), dramatically enhanced curb appeal boosting home values $15,000-$25,000, and zero maintenance requirements. Tile upgrade makes most sense when: you're planning 15+ years in your home, your roof structure can support tile weight (we assess this during inspection), and you value aesthetics and long-term cost savings over minimal upfront cost."
